        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add Pioneer.ai as an inference provider with live model discovery",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nOpenClaw had no support for Pioneer.ai as an inference provider. Users with Pioneer.ai accounts could not use it as a model source, and there was no way to browse or select Pioneer models from the UI model picker.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThis PR adds Pioneer.ai as a first-class OpenClaw inference provider with live model discovery:\n\n- **Pioneer plugin** (`extensions/pioneer/`) registers Pioneer.ai as an OpenAI-compatible provider at `https://api.pioneer.ai/v1`. Authentication uses a `PIONEER_API_KEY` env var or auth profile.\n- **Live model discovery via `augmentModelCatalog`** — The `augmentModelCatalog` hook calls the Pioneer `/v1/models` endpoint (returns `{ data: [...] }` — standard OpenAI-compatible shape parsed by the shared `getCachedLiveProviderModelRows` helper) when a Pioneer API key is configured. This is the hook that the gateway's `loadModelCatalog` → `augmentModelCatalogWithProviderPlugins` path calls, which is what feeds the UI model picker. The `catalog.run` hook (`buildPioneerCatalogResult`) is used by the CLI `models list --provider pioneer` path.\n- **60-second TTL model cache** — `getCachedLiveProviderModelRows` caches live model rows for 60 seconds per provider. New models appear within one cache TTL without a gateway restart.\n- **Gateway catalog warm** — A startup sidecar pre-warms the gateway model catalog on startup (read-only then full-discovery, no recurring loop) so the full Pioneer model list is available in the UI picker from the first open.\n- **Provider wildcard allowlist** — Onboarding sets `pioneer/*` in `agents.defaults.models` so all live-discovered Pioneer models are visible in the picker without enumerating them individually.\n- **Default model** — `pioneer/auto` is set as the default primary at onboard time, routing each request to the best available Pioneer model automatically.\n- **`normalizeResolvedModel` hook** — Rewrites bare `auto` → `pioneer/auto` at transport time so the Pioneer API receives the correct routing alias.\n\n## User Impact\n\n- Users can now add Pioneer.ai as an inference provider and use any of its 78+ models.\n- The UI model picker shows the full live Pioneer model list after gateway startup.\n- New Pioneer models appear automatically within the 60s model cache TTL — no gateway restart needed.\n- `pioneer/auto` as the default model means users get the best Pioneer model without manually selecting one.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Live API contract** — Pioneer `/v1/models` returns `{ data: [...], first_id, last_id, has_more, object, models }` with standard OpenAI list pagination. The `data` key contains model rows with `id`, `display_name`, `max_input_tokens`, `max_tokens`, `capabilities`, etc. The shared `getCachedLiveProviderModelRows` helper parses `data` arrays by default, so no custom `readRows` override is needed.\n\n**`pnpm openclaw models list --provider pioneer`** (auth key redacted):\n```\nModel                                      Input      Ctx         Local Auth  Tags\npioneer/anthropic/pioneer-auto             text       1024k       no    yes\npioneer/auto                               text       1024k       no    yes   default\npioneer/claude-3-7-sonnet-latest           text       8k          no    yes\npioneer/claude-haiku-4-5                   text       195k        no    yes\npioneer/claude-opus-4-1                    text       195k        no    yes\npioneer/claude-opus-4-5                    text       195k        no    yes\npioneer/claude-opus-4-6                    text       977k        no    yes\npioneer/claude-opus-4-8                    text       977k        no    yes\npioneer/claude-sonnet-4-6                  text       977k        no    yes\npioneer/deepseek-ai/DeepSeek-V3.1          text       160k        no    yes\npioneer/deepseek-ai/DeepSeek-V4-Flash      text       977k        no    yes\npioneer/deepseek-ai/DeepSeek-V4-Pro        text       977k        no    yes\npioneer/gemini-3-flash                     text       1024k       no    yes\npioneer/gemini-3.5-flash                   text       1024k       no    yes\n... (78 models total via live discovery)\n```\n\n**Gateway UI catalog** — SQLite `agent_model_catalogs` shows 21KB cached entries (full live catalog) vs the previous 2-model static result (confirmed by cache size and model count check via CLI).\n\n**Tests:**\n- `extensions/pioneer/provider-catalog.test.ts` — 9 tests covering live catalog building, static-only model injection, ID normalization, fallback behavior\n- `extensions/pioneer/index.test.ts` — 5 tests covering plugin registration, onboard config, and `normalizeResolvedModel` (auto → pioneer/auto transport rewrite)\n- `src/commands/models/list.provider-catalog.test.ts` — 25 tests pass (unchanged)",
        "branch": "feat/pioneer-live-model-discovery",
